This paper discusses resource isolation for mobile security and privacy, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on implementing isolation in the Android Framework, which involves operating system (cs.OS) and system-level design (cs.SY) considerations. Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency and performance of the isolation strategy, which could also fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
